Privacy Policy for SPECRES Bot

Last updated: January 5, 2026

1. Introduction
SPECRES Bot ("we", "our", or "the Application") is a private automation tool that integrates with Google services (Google Sheets, Google Drive) for internal business purposes.

2. Data We Access
The Application accesses only:
- Google Sheets: to read and write spreadsheet data
- Google Drive: to create, read, and manage files

3. How We Use Data
All data accessed through Google APIs is used solely for:
- Processing user requests within the automation workflow
- Creating and managing spreadsheet reports
- Storing files in designated Google Drive folders

4. Data Storage
- We do not store Google user data on external servers
- All data remains within Google's infrastructure
- Temporary processing data is deleted after workflow completion

5. Data Sharing
We do not sell, trade, or share any data accessed through Google APIs with third parties.

6. Data Security
We implement appropriate security measures to protect against unauthorized access to data.

7. User Rights
Users can revoke access to their Google account at any time through Google Account settings (https://myaccount.google.com/permissions).

8. Limited Use Disclosure
SPECRES Bot's use and transfer of information received from Google APIs adheres to Google API Services User Data Policy, including the Limited Use requirements.

9. Contact
For questions about this Privacy Policy, contact: [your-email@example.com]

10. Changes
We may update this Privacy Policy. Changes will be posted on this page with updated date.
